                        <p> <hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE 3.&#8212;<name type="person">Private Thomas Shea</name>, <name type="organization">Co. F, 4th Minn.</name>; age
                                25; was admitted <date type="admit" when="1865-02-16">Feb. 16, 1865</date>, with pneumonia.  He
                                progressed satisfactorily until <date type="injury" when="1865-02-21">the 21st</date>, when white
                                deposits appeared upon the throat.  He died on <date type="death" when="1865-02-25">the 25th</date>.  <hi rend="italic">Post-mortem</hi> examination: Membranes of brain fully injected.
                                        Pharynx dark-purple; tonsils with patches of thick white
                                        deposit. Right lung crepitant but coated with yellow lymph;
                                        upper lobe of left lung solidified and bronchial tubes
                                        dark-colored. Heart adherent and some yellow serum in
                                        pericardium. Liver small, an&#230;mic, with old adhesions;
                                        spleen soft, pale, granular; kidneys fatty.&#8212;<hi rend="italic"><name type="hospital" key="189">Third Division Hospital</name>, <name type="place">Alexandria, Va.</name></hi>  </p>                        
